fastahack
------------------------------------------
fastahack is a small application for indexing and extracting sequences and
subsequences from FASTA files. The included Fasta.cpp library provides a FASTA
reader and indexer that can be embedded into applications which would benefit
from directly reading subsequences from FASTA files. The library automatically
handles index file generation and use.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ekg/fastahack

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ekg/fastahack/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fastahack-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fastahack-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fastahack-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fastahack-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fastahack)
  /usr/bin/fastahack.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fastahack.README
  /usr/share/doc/fastahack/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/fastahack/README

